{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Need a mic, too, huh?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, this town, Comlausa, you're not going to find it on any map.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's a small village, which consisted of 26 Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe the entire village, maybe were about 200, maybe, families all together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most of them were Romanian people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My family-- we were eight in my immediate family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My-- my parents-- mother, father-- and I had four brothers and a sister.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I was born in 1928.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at that time, this village was part of Romania.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The-- the village had one old schoolhouse, which was rebuilt in the mid-'30s.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember going to the old one and also to the new one.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But most of our-- the emphasis was not put on-- on-- on secular education.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The emphasis was put more on the Yiddish education.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In other words, we had a cheder there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And even so we were only 26 families, my village always prided itself of having one of the best cheders for the entire area.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, there were villages which are much larger than my village.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They would send their children to my village.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We had two cheders.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "One cheder was [HEBREW] Melamed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This Melamed, his name was Reb Moishele.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He was a small fellow, and he hardly made a living.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But they would pay, it was called [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They would pay so much for a season to send the children there to-- to study.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I believe we started-- when you were 3 years old, you know, they used to shave off your head.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And then you had Peahs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So they went to the-- they went to cheder, to Moishele.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Moishele, and his wife's name was [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Fega. ?] And there we studied [? all ?] [? of ?] [? base, ?] oh, until the age of about 7, 8 years old.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "From there, we went to another cheder, where this was more advanced.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And even so, when I was 9 years, 10 years old, my-- see, over there, there were no classes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "You went to a cheder to-- everybody went to the same class, to the same class.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But the studies-- the-- everybody studied as much as his capacity could-- could-- could-- could absorb.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "My friends who studied with me, even so when I was 10 years old, they were three, four years older than me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Not ?] [? with-- ?] I had tremendous capacity to study the weekly Seder, [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And not only did we have to study it from the book, but we had to know it by heart.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Cames Thursday afternoon, you knew the Gemara, Gemara [HEBREW], with all the commentaries, by heart.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I still remember it because if you didn't know it Thursday, they would beat you mercilessly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "If they would do the same in the United States, that teacher would be locked up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But over there, apparently, maybe it was a good system because otherwise, I wouldn't have remembered it even to this day.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Whatever I know-- and I want you to know that I went to-- to cheder, to Jewish schools, until the age of 12.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I think I'm capable of-- of having a conversation with-- with any rabbi, when it comes to Talmud and to-- and to Jewish studies.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And apparently-- apparently-- the system must've been-- must have had something good.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So most-- again, most of the concentration of my village was strictly Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, over there, when it came a Shabbos or a Rosh Hashanah, or a Pesach, you didn't have to look at the calendar what-- what-- when it's going to be Pesach.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You felt it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was in the air.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was in the air, every holiday.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had a synagogue in Comlausa where they send over three men that was at, like-- like-- during World War I to America.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they made money here.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they send it back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They saved it up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And with that money, that was the seed money to build a shul, a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The people-- everybody got involved in building it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, it was built before I was born.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was finished in 1925.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the people, they went to the mountains, they-- they-- they-- to cut stone and wood.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they worked there for years and years until they build this up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The walls were about a meter thick, which is over 3 feet thick, the walls.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "High ceilings.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "On the ceilings there was painted stars.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Around the-- around-- around the synagogue, on the wall, they used to have the-- the zodiac-- the zodiac.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Every month had a, you know, like the fish, the chicken, the whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It had all around, all around, all around the-- the main shul, the main synagogue.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
